5: What location did you decide on?
9:
A spot in the heart of the city proved
difficult to secure, but I did manage
to find a spacious lot next to a park.
11:
The city is still under construction, so
I have no doubt it will become a
prime location in time. There will be
no shortage of opportunities.
15:
You've really outdone yourself,
haven't you?
18:
I saw an opportunity and I seized it.
Claudius also—
29: Hey! Watch where you're going, kid!
44:
Check it out! I managed to swipe all
this cash!
46:
W-we can finally eat something
good again!
48:
...What about that other person? Will
they be okay without their money?
50:
Of course not! But they deserve it!
Those nasty felines are always
causing trouble for us poor dogfolk.
52:
That's why we're here to collect, as
usual.
54:
B-but we already paid our
protection money the other day!
56:
Is that so? You're pretty ballsy for a
nobody.
63:
No, on second thought, "thief" is far
too generous. Thieves aren't usually
THIS pathetic.
70:
Drop the money, pups. I'm not in the
mood for any ruff-housing.
74:
I'm afraid you lot will require some
quiet time behind bars before we
can let you go.
79:
Fine work, Albert. Now, if only you
dropped the good boy act, I
wouldn't have any complaints.
83:
I swore I'd never fight like an animal
again.
90:
Would you kittens like to end up the
same as your friends here?
99:
Well, well. Looks we've got quite a lot
of newcomers today.
101:
Welcome to your new home,
children.
105:
No need to worry, I've already been
paid in full. There's no need for you
to do things you don't want to
anymore.
107:
Now please, come in. I'd like to show
you around.
110:
Things proceeded ahead of
schedule, but I'm glad to see the
facility complete now.
113:
I'm impressed. It looks just like the
orphanage in Palpebra, doesn't it?
117:
This will be a place where dogfolk,
catfolk, and many others will live
together in peace. Much better than
squabbling in the streets over
scraps.
123:
I do, but... Was the money I put
together really enough?
127:
I'll admit I was surprised when I
found out what you had in mind.
Setting up an orphanage with the
money you saved up in Palpebra.
135:
It wasn't enough, was it? I have
some more saved up, if—
139:
Now hold on a moment. We've
received state funding for this
project, and I want to return the
money you've already given.
142:
Relying on the good will of
individuals indefinitely is a losing
strategy in politics.
145:
There will eventually come a day
where we must rely on that good
will, but that day is not today.
Consider this matter concluded.
151:
All the same, I don't know what to do
with myself now. All I can do is fight,
so what good am—
155:
There's plenty of work for you to do.
Surely this city needs someone with
your disposition and skillset.
163:
Teo does. Claudius and myself as
well. We need people just like you.
167: You know what I've done, Albert.
171:
Do you truly believe we must
discard those with a flawed past in
order to build a future?
174:
That we cannot move forward
without making outcasts of the
wounded, the lost, and the infirm?
176:
What nonsense. Wounds heal and
blood can be washed away!
This is what Claudius and I fight for!
180:
And you will keep believing that
even after you've won?
184:
Of course. That's how it is on other
worlds, after all.
188:
...Oh dear. I really mustn't keep
allowing myself to be lectured by
pups.
191:
I'm saying that I'm happy to help,
Albert.
195:
You have my gratitude!
...But...
Could you stop referring to me as a
"pup?"
198:
I'm afraid not. Maybe when you're a
little older.
201:
Anyway. How can I be of assistance
from now on?
205:
O-oh! Yes, well, if you could just take
a look here...
